WEBVTT

1
00:00:03.600 --> 00:00:12.960
Hope for the best, plan for the worst. This one tool sizes
your entire account around the single worst thing that can
happen to you, so that when it does, you survive it.

2
00:00:13.560 --> 00:00:28.320
It's the Doomsday Budget, folded right into the Prop
Simulator. It finds the worst losing streak this move can
throw at you, the larger of what actually happened in
history and a brutal Monte Carlo worst case, and then
builds your whole plan around surviving exactly that.

3
00:00:28.920 --> 00:00:41.160
And the math is beautifully simple. Worst Loss Streak,
times your Risk per Trade, equals your Doomsday Drawdown.
The deepest hole a single account has to absorb. That is
the number your account size must be able to survive.

4
00:00:41.760 --> 00:00:55.008
Then it asks the one question that really matters. Does
that hole fit inside a single account's drawdown cap?
Green means yes, with headroom to spare. Red means one
account would bust, and you need a rotation of accounts to
share the streak between them.

5
00:00:55.608 --> 00:01:05.712
And it spells out exactly what survives. The capital to
hold in reserve, how many accounts to rotate, and the
position size that fits. Concrete numbers, not vague
advice.

6
00:01:06.312 --> 00:01:20.208
Here's the whole philosophy. Survive doomsday, and the
other ninety nine percent of the time is gravy. Most
traders size for the good days and get wiped out by the
bad streak. This sizes for the bad streak, so the good
days take care of themselves.

7
00:01:20.808 --> 00:01:24.432
Plan for your worst streak. Everything better than that is
just profit.
